D) Why this crosses from "intertextuality" to your technical "plagiarism‑equivalence"
O(1) translators exist for each pair (small dictionaries of mytheme rewrites).
Coherent clusters of rare, structured elements occur (e.g., Flood: bitumen + bird test + sacrifice + aroma + post‑flood sign).
Directionality appears (earlier attestation, lexical bridges, preserved idiosyncrasies).
Algorithmic‑information argument: two independently drawn narratives of size S almost never admit mutual O(1) recodings; yet we can exhibit them here. Independence is thus measure‑zero under reasonable ensembles.
Hence, in your technical sense, the later Hebrew narratives are plagiarism‑equivalent recodings of earlier Mesopotamian materials (no claim about intent or legal wrong---these are ancient, public‑domain traditions).
